▶ {Qo'noS wo':sen:nolink}
   {tlhIngan wo' Degh 'oH Deghvam'e'. tlhIngan Dujmey law'qu' SommeyDaq batlh cha'lu'. juHqo' Qo'noSvo' loghDaq lengtaHvIS tlhInganpu' 'ej qo'mey Sar charghtaHvIS chaH Dat tlhIngan may'Duj luleghDI' neH qIb nganpu' buQpu' may'Duj 'ej ghIjpu' 'oH. nIteb ghIjpu' je Deghvam.:sen:nolink}
  "Empire of Kronos
   This marking represents the Klingon Empire and has been emblazoned upon the hulls of countless Klingon Starships. During the aggressive expansion of the Klingon people from their homeworld of Kronos into space, this symbol grew to become as feared throughout the galaxy as the menacing profiles of their battlecruisers."[2]

There are five types of noun suffixes in Klingon.

Noun Type 1: Augmentative/diminutive
▶ {-'a':n:suff}
▶ {-Hom:n:suff}
▶ {-oy:n:suff}

Noun Type 2: Number
▶ {-pu':n:suff}
▶ {-Du':n:suff}
▶ {-mey:n:suff}

Noun Type 3: Qualification
▶ {-qoq:n:suff}
▶ {-Hey:n:suff}
▶ {-na':n:suff}

Noun Type 4: Possession/specification
▶ {-wIj:n:suff} / {-wI':n:suff}
▶ {-lIj:n:suff} / {-lI':n:suff}
▶ {-maj:n:suff} / {-ma':n:suff}
▶ {-raj:n:suff} / {-ra':n:suff}
▶ {-Daj:n:suff}
▶ {-chaj:n:suff}
▶ {-vam:n:suff}
▶ {-vetlh:n:suff}

Noun Type 5: Syntactic markers
▶ {-Daq:n:suff}
▶ {-vo':n:suff}
▶ {-mo':n:suff}
▶ {-vaD:n:suff}
▶ {-'e':n:suff}

The joke goes like this:

▶ {Doq'a' SuvwI'pu'?:sen:nolink}
  "Are warriors red?"

▶ {ghobe'. SuD.}
  "No. They are green."

